{"id":15468,"date":"2013-07-29T11:15:00","date_gmt":"2013-07-29T07:15:00","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/www.dailyhadithonline.com\/?p=15468"},"modified":"2025-03-18T11:18:50","modified_gmt":"2025-03-18T07:18:50","slug":"fear-allah-animals-ride","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/07\/29\/fear-allah-animals-ride\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Animals: Fear Allah in creatures you own"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Abdullah ibn Ja\u2019far reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, entered a garden among the Ansar. When a camel saw the Prophet, it\u00a0started weeping and making sounds as its tears flowed. The Prophet came to it and patted it on the head, so it became silent. The Prophet said, \u201c<strong>Who is the master of this camel? To whom does it belong?<\/strong>\u201d A young man from the Ansar came and said, \u201cThis is mine, O Messenger of Allah.\u201d The Prophet said, \u201c<b>Do you not fear Allah in this animal whom Allah has placed in your possession? She has complained to me that you keep her hungry and tired<\/b>.\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: Sunan Abi\u0304 Da\u0304wu\u0304d 2549<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <b><i>Sahih<\/i><\/b> (authentic) according to Al-Arna&#8217;ut<\/p>\n<p align=\"right\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0639\u064e\u0628\u0652\u062f\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u0650 \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u062c\u064e\u0639\u0652\u0641\u064e\u0631\u064d \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0641\u064e\u062f\u064e\u062e\u064e\u0644\u064e \u062d\u064e\u0627\u0626\u0650\u0637\u064b\u0627 \u0644\u0650\u0631\u064e\u062c\u064f\u0644\u064d \u0645\u0650\u0646\u0652 \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0623\u064e\u0646\u0652\u0635\u064e\u0627\u0631\u0650 \u0641\u064e\u0625\u0650\u0630\u064e\u0627 \u062c\u064e\u0645\u064e\u0644\u064c \u0641\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0645\u064e\u0651\u0627 \u0631\u064e\u0623\u064e\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0646\u064e\u0651\u0628\u0650\u064a\u064e\u0651 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u06